cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with learning vector representations of text that are compatible between different languages. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a scheme to map word vectors using an adversarial autoencoder. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves natural language processing and semantic analysis. The paper also mentions the possibility of future developments in cross-lingual sentence representations, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
